"{\"uid\": \"uk.news.yahoo.com-tahitis-olympic-surfing-venue-polynesians-090606030.html\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Manage your account By Lincoln Feast TEAHUPO'O, Tahiti (Reuters) - On the remote south coast of Tahiti, its Jurassic peaks and azure lagoon accessible only by boat, Patrick Rochette is explaining how centuries-old Polynesian conservation traditions are being revived to protect this unique environment.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 312, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 32, \"end\": 39, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abraham_Lincoln\", \"score\": 0.9999998065518599, \"rank\": 1.9344830952537767e-07, \"text\": \"Lincoln\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abraham_Lincoln\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abraham_Lincoln\"}, {\"begin\": 66, \"end\": 73, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 0.9999999999408828, \"rank\": 5.892437776653198e-11, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 106, \"end\": 112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9999999969791133, \"rank\": 3.0207707151943693e-09, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}, {\"begin\": 175, \"end\": 182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Star\", \"score\": 0.9995675986524415, \"rank\": 0.0004324310448047806, \"text\": \"Patrick\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Star\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Star\"}, {\"begin\": 224, \"end\": 234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.84505248179367, \"rank\": 0.18062779365176826, \"text\": \"Polynesian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your account\", \"from\": 7, \"to\": 19}, {\"ngram\": \"(Reuters\", \"from\": 55, \"to\": 63}, {\"ngram\": \"Tahiti\", \"from\": 96, \"to\": 102}, {\"ngram\": \"lagoon\", \"from\": 133, \"to\": 139}, {\"ngram\": \"boat\", \"from\": 159, \"to\": 163}, {\"ngram\": \"this unique environment\", \"from\": 278, \"to\": 301}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mingled with gruesome tales of the island's history of tribal wars and the roots of wave-riding, it's a compelling account that resonates with the school children that the Tahitian elder has brought to this idyllic spot close to the Olympic surfing venue of Teahupo'o.\", \"from\": 314, \"to\": 582, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 486, \"end\": 494, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.7561434838155143, \"rank\": 0.3225003208998684, \"text\": \"Tahitian\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"gruesome tales\", \"from\": 327, \"to\": 341}, {\"ngram\": \"the island's history\", \"from\": 345, \"to\": 365}, {\"ngram\": \"tribal wars\", \"from\": 369, \"to\": 380}, {\"ngram\": \"the roots\", \"from\": 385, \"to\": 394}, {\"ngram\": \"wave-riding\", \"from\": 398, \"to\": 409}, {\"ngram\": \"a compelling account\", \"from\": 416, \"to\": 436}, {\"ngram\": \"the school children\", \"from\": 457, \"to\": 476}, {\"ngram\": \"this idyllic spot\", \"from\": 516, \"to\": 533}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic surfing venue\", \"from\": 543, \"to\": 568}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 572, \"to\": 581}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among the interconnected Polynesian concepts lost or repressed during Tahiti's French colonisation that Rochette describes: respect for tupuna, the ancestors; mana, the spiritual power of people and places; tapu, that which is sacred; rahui, a restriction or prohibition; and the guardians - the whales, sharks, turtles.\", \"from\": 584, \"to\": 904, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 609, \"end\": 619, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.84505248179367, \"rank\": 0.18062779365176826, \"text\": \"Polynesian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\"}, {\"begin\": 654, \"end\": 660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9999999969791133, \"rank\": 3.0207707151943693e-09, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}, {\"begin\": 663, \"end\": 682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_colonial_empire\", \"score\": 0.9999999998331077, \"rank\": 1.6674761786490068e-10, \"text\": \"French colonisation\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_colonial_empire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_colonial_empire\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Rochette\", \"from\": 688, \"to\": 696}, {\"ngram\": \"respect\", \"from\": 708, \"to\": 715}, {\"ngram\": \"tupuna\", \"from\": 720, \"to\": 726}, {\"ngram\": \"the ancestors\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 741}, {\"ngram\": \"mana\", \"from\": 743, \"to\": 747}, {\"ngram\": \"the spiritual power\", \"from\": 749, \"to\": 768}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 772, \"to\": 778}, {\"ngram\": \"places\", \"from\": 783, \"to\": 789}, {\"ngram\": \"tapu\", \"from\": 791, \"to\": 795}, {\"ngram\": \"a restriction\", \"from\": 826, \"to\": 839}, {\"ngram\": \"prohibition\", \"from\": 843, \"to\": 854}, {\"ngram\": \"the guardians\", \"from\": 860, \"to\": 873}, {\"ngram\": \"the whales\", \"from\": 876, \"to\": 886}, {\"ngram\": \"sharks\", \"from\": 888, \"to\": 894}, {\"ngram\": \"turtles\", \"from\": 896, \"to\": 903}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's up to the children to go home with this information and explain it to their parents,\\\" says Rochette, a burly 63-year-old.\", \"from\": 906, \"to\": 1033, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the children\", \"from\": 918, \"to\": 930}, {\"ngram\": \"this information\", \"from\": 947, \"to\": 963}, {\"ngram\": \"their parents\", \"from\": 982, \"to\": 995}, {\"ngram\": \"Rochette\", \"from\": 1003, \"to\": 1011}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For Rochette and others, countering the pressures of over-exploitation and climate change go hand-in-hand with a cultural renaissance in the Pacific island group, a distinct Polynesian identity that spans the world's largest ocean.\", \"from\": 1035, \"to\": 1266, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1209, \"end\": 1219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.84505248179367, \"rank\": 0.18062779365176826, \"text\": \"Polynesian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Rochette\", \"from\": 1039, \"to\": 1047}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 1052, \"to\": 1058}, {\"ngram\": \"the pressures\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1084}, {\"ngram\": \"over-exploitation\", \"from\": 1088, \"to\": 1105}, {\"ngram\": \"climate change\", \"from\": 1110, \"to\": 1124}, {\"ngram\": \"hand\", \"from\": 1136, \"to\": 1140}, {\"ngram\": \"a cultural renaissance\", \"from\": 1146, \"to\": 1168}, {\"ngram\": \"the Pacific island group\", \"from\": 1172, \"to\": 1196}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's largest ocean\", \"from\": 1240, \"to\": 1265}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We Polynesians, in 15 or 20 years, if we do not do anything, there'll be nothing left,\\\" Rochette said in a boat, speeding down the jungle-clad coast.\", \"from\": 1268, \"to\": 1418, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1272, \"end\": 1283, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.7950617145173403, \"rank\": 0.2574707460743033, \"text\": \"Polynesians\", \"types\": [], \"wi