{\"ngram\": \"almost everyone\", \"from\": 4332, \"to\": 4347}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ten years ago, however, the reef was struggling.\", \"from\": 4367, \"to\": 4415, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the reef\", \"from\": 4391, \"to\": 4399}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Plagued by over-fishing and hit more frequently by damaging storms, a decision was made by the community to re-introduce a rahui over a 768-hectare area south of the village, banning fishing and other activities.\", \"from\": 4417, \"to\": 4629, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"over-fishing\", \"from\": 4428, \"to\": 4440}, {\"ngram\": \"damaging storms\", \"from\": 4468, \"to\": 4483}, {\"ngram\": \"a decision\", \"from\": 4485, \"to\": 4495}, {\"ngram\": \"the community\", \"from\": 4508, \"to\": 4521}, {\"ngram\": \"a rahui\", \"from\": 4538, \"to\": 4545}, {\"ngram\": \"a 768-hectare area\", \"from\": 4551, \"to\": 4569}, {\"ngram\": \"the village\", \"from\": 4579, \"to\": 4590}, {\"ngram\": \"fishing and other activities\", \"from\": 4600, \"to\": 4628}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In the older culture, it was the king who decided these things and you could not go against it, you would be killed,\\\" and many people were afraid of the concept, said Rochette, who manages the Teahupo'o rahui.\", \"from\": 4631, \"to\": 4841, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the older culture\", \"from\": 4635, \"to\": 4652}, {\"ngram\": \"the king\", \"from\": 4661, \"to\": 4669}, {\"ngram\": \"these things\", \"from\": 4682, \"to\": 4694}, {\"ngram\": \"many people\", \"from\": 4754, \"to\": 4765}, {\"ngram\": \"the concept\", \"from\": 4781, \"to\": 4792}, {\"ngram\": \"Rochette\", \"from\": 4799, \"to\": 4807}, {\"ngram\": \"the Teahupo'o rahui\", \"from\": 4821, \"to\": 4840}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The approach has been modernised and democratised, with the communities across French Polynesia now instigating rahui and deciding how to operate them to sustain their environment and resources.\", \"from\": 4843, \"to\": 5037, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4929, \"end\": 4938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.6496984050798375e-16, \"text\": \"Polynesia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The approach\", \"from\": 4843, \"to\": 4855}, {\"ngram\": \"the communities\", \"from\": 4899, \"to\": 4914}, {\"ngram\": \"rahui\", \"from\": 4955, \"to\": 4960}, {\"ngram\": \"their environment\", \"from\": 5005, \"to\": 5022}, {\"ngram\": \"resources\", \"from\": 5027, \"to\": 5036}]}, {\"sentence\": \"South of Teahupo'o, buoys are set out to mark the rahui limits, and locals monitor the zone to ensure compliance.\", \"from\": 5039, \"to\": 5152, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 5048, \"to\": 5057}, {\"ngram\": \"buoys\", \"from\": 5059, \"to\": 5064}, {\"ngram\": \"the rahui limits\", \"from\": 5085, \"to\": 5101}, {\"ngram\": \"locals\", \"from\": 5107, \"to\": 5113}, {\"ngram\": \"the zone\", \"from\": 5122, \"to\": 5130}, {\"ngram\": \"compliance\", \"from\": 5141, \"to\": 5151}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They say the impact has been mostly positive, with the reef thriving and fish stocks improving.\", \"from\": 5153, \"to\": 5248, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the impact\", \"from\": 5162, \"to\": 5172}, {\"ngram\": \"stocks\", \"from\": 5231, \"to\": 5237}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Scrambling over streams and paths of broken coral, Rochette tells the story of a sacred rock and its role in ancestral fishing rituals, recounts battles that turned the lagoon red with blood and details how surfing was introduced here by twin brothers.\", \"from\": 5250, \"to\": 5502, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"streams\", \"from\": 5266, \"to\": 5273}, {\"ngram\": \"paths\", \"from\": 5278, \"to\": 5283}, {\"ngram\": \"broken coral\", \"from\": 5287, \"to\": 5299}, {\"ngram\": \"Rochette\", \"from\": 5301, \"to\": 5309}, {\"ngram\": \"the story\", \"from\": 5316, \"to\": 5325}, {\"ngram\": \"a sacred rock\", \"from\": 5329, \"to\": 5342}, {\"ngram\": \"its role\", \"from\": 5347, \"to\": 5355}, {\"ngram\": \"ancestral fishing rituals\", \"from\": 5359, \"to\": 5384}, {\"ngram\": \"recounts battles\", \"from\": 5386, \"to\": 5402}, {\"ngram\": \"the lagoon\", \"from\": 5415, \"to\": 5425}, {\"ngram\": \"blood\", \"from\": 5435, \"to\": 5440}, {\"ngram\": \"details\", \"from\": 5445, \"to\": 5452}, {\"ngram\": \"how surfing\", \"from\": 5453, \"to\": 5464}, {\"ngram\": \"twin brothers\", \"from\": 5488, \"to\": 5501}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the cultural aspects have been significant, ascribing an economic value to the environment has also been important.\", \"from\": 5504, \"to\": 5625, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the cultural aspects\", \"from\": 5510, \"to\": 5530}, {\"ngram\": \"an economic value\", \"from\": 5564, \"to\": 5581}, {\"ngram\": \"the environment\", \"from\": 5585, \"to\": 5600}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cliff Kapono, a Hawaiian coral scientist, surfer and Polynesian activist, worked with locals to map and value the economic impact that works around the Olympics could have on the reef and lagoon using an established formula.\", \"from\": 5627, \"to\": 5851, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5633, \"end\": 5639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keola_Beamer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kapono\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keola_Beamer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keola_Beamer\"}, {\"begin\": 5643, \"end\": 5651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaiian_language\", \"score\": 0.9959180247021527, \"rank\": 0.004098451554917553, \"text\": \"Hawaiian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaiian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaiian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 5680, \"end\": 5690, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.84505248179367, \"rank\": 0.18062779365176826, \"text\": \"Polynesian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"surfer\", \"from\": 5669, \"to\": 5675}, {\"ngram\": \"locals\", \"from\": 5713, \"to\": 5719}, {\"ngram\": \"the economic impact\", \"from\": 5737, \"to\": 5756}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 5775, \"to\": 5787}, {\"ngram\": \"the reef\", \"from\": 5802, \"to\": 5810}, {\"ngram\": \"lagoon\", \"from\": 5815, \"to\": 5821}, {\"ngram\": \"an established formula\", \"from\": 5828, \"to\": 5850}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kapono's MEGA Lab estimated a direct economic impact of $170,000 for disturbing and destroying corals at the judging tower site and $1.3 million in total for the wider reef disruption around Teahupo'o from dredging and other works.\", \"from\": 5853, \"to\": 6084, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5853, \"end\": 5859, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keola_Beamer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kapono\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keola_Beamer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keola_Beamer\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a direct economic impact\", \"from\": 5881, \"to\": 5905}, {\"ngram\": \"corals\", \"from\": 5948, \"to\": 5954}, {\"ngram\": \"the judging tower site\", \"from\": 5958, \"to\": 5980}, {\"ngram\": \"total\", \"from\": 6001, \"to\": 6006}, {\"ngram\": \"the wider reef disruption\", \"from\": 6011, \"to\": 6036}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 6044, \"to\": 6053}, {\"ngram\": \"dredging\", \"from\": 6059, \"to\": 6067}, {\"ngram\": \"other works\", \"from\": 6072, \"to\": 6083}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Beyond the economics, the idea of being guardians of the ocean was intrinsic to the Polynesian philosophy, Kapono said.\", \"from\": 